{
  "name": "Iron Knuckle",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Taijutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You perform a single high-powered strike with full intention to cause harm. Make a melee taijutsu attack. On a hit, you deal your [Unarmed Damage] + 2d6 and force the target to make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, you knock them back a number of feet equal to 5 x your Strength ability modifier.</p><p>If this jutsu is used as a Finisher, you instead deal your [Unarmed Damage] + 4d6 and on a failed save they are knocked back a number of feet equal to 10 x your Strength ability modifier and if they strike a solid surface that is less than 5 feet thick, they break through it if they have 10 or more feet remaining to be knocked back, taking 3d6 bludgeoning damage.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above D-Rank increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the damage by 1d6</p>",
